Load kNN species layers from online data repository

Source: R/maps.R
loadkNNSpeciesLayers.Rd

TODO: description needed

loadkNNSpeciesLayers(dPath, rasterToMatch, studyArea, sppEquiv,
  knnNamesCol = "KNN", sppEquivCol, thresh = 1, url, ...)

Arguments

dPath

path to the data directory
rasterToMatch

passed to prepInputs
studyArea

passed to prepInputs
sppEquiv

table with species name equivalencies between the kNN format and the final naming format. See data("sppEquivalencies_CA", "pemisc").
knnNamesCol

character string indicating the column in sppEquiv containing kNN species names. Default "KNN" for when sppEquivalencies_CA is used.
sppEquivCol

character string indicating the column in sppEquiv to use for final species names.
thresh

the minimum number of pixels where the species must have biomass > 0 to be considered present in the study area. Defaults to 1.
url

the source url for the data, passed to prepInputs
...

Additonal arguments passed to Cache and equivalentName.

Value

A raster stack of percent cover layers by species.
